			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Tea Processing;Tea Production,精制茶</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:category level="0">Materials production</common:category>
					<common:category level="1">Food and renewable raw materials</common:category>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Tea leaves go through a refining process before being packaged and sold. The refining of tea involves five stages: Withering, Rolling, Oxidation, Drying and Sorting &amp; Grading. In Japan, the refining process is usually done by the tea wholesalers and consists of three basic steps: firing, sorting, and blending. The Tea Refinement Process, also known as tea processing or tea production, is the series of steps involved in transforming freshly harvested tea leaves into the final product.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">茶叶在被包装和销售之前需要经过精炼过程。茶叶的精炼包括五个阶段：萎凋、揉捻、氧化、干燥和分级。在日本，精炼过程通常由茶叶批发商完成，包括三个基本步骤：烘焙、分选和混合。茶叶精炼过程，也被称为茶叶加工或茶叶生产，是将新鲜采摘的茶叶转化为最终产品的一系列步骤。</common:generalComment>
